parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can cause accidents or injuries when reversing, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles or pedestrians behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The backup camera displays a black screen
a camera with a line through it
making it impossible to use when reversing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, including loss of motive power, unintended activation of systems, and failure of critical safety features.
symptoms: causing issues such as the headlights
or air conditioning to turn on or off unexpectedly
or the speedometer to display inaccurate readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: causing issues such as the screen freezing
failing to respond to touch commands

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake system can cause accidents or injuries, as the vehicle may not be able to stop properly.
symptoms: causing issues such as the brakes feeling like they won't stop

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the window system can cause safety issues, such as the inability to escape in an emergency.
symptoms: causing issues such as the rear passenger side window not going down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning backup camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries while reversing, especially for pedestrians, children, or pets.
Unintended vehicle movement can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is in gear or in motion.
symptoms: Vehicle shifts into reverse gear unintentionally
or the gear shifter is easily knocked into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can cause serious injuries or fatalities, as well as property damage.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the AC vent

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire failure can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially at high speeds.
Transmission and performance issues can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially when driving uphill or merging.
The lack of a backup camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries while reversing, especially for pedestrians, children, or pets.
symptoms: Vehicle not equipped with a backup camera

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended door unlocking can compromise vehicle security and safety, especially for solo drivers or families with children.
symptoms: Doors automatically unlock when the vehicle is turned off or on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning all-wheel drive and ABS systems can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially in inclement weather.
symptoms: Rear of the vehicle feels like it's slipping on ice
and the vehicle takes time to pick up speed after starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ingress of moisture into the headlight assembly can cause the headlights to malfunction, reducing nighttime visibility and increasing the risk of accidents. Repeated failure of the headlight bulbs can lead to additional safety risks.
symptoms: Water or condensation accumulation inside the headlight housing
headlights surging or dimming while in use.
